body_text:
This will use a CPOW (cross process wrapper) now that this is really running in the child process. We're aiming to get rid of those.
Instead, you can use:
ContentTask.spawn(browser, null, () => {
  content.document.getElementById("shield-studies-update-preferences").click();
});
which will run that function in the content process (as a new frame script, essentially).

body:
This will use a CPOW (cross process wrapper) now that this is really running in the child process. We're aiming to get rid of those.

Instead, you can use:
```js
ContentTask.spawn(browser, null, () => {
  content.document.getElementById("shield-studies-update-preferences").click();
});
```
which will run that function in the content process (as a new frame script, essentially).
